<p>I wanted to find the sum of two arrays in JavaScript at the same index location (ex. arr1[0] + arr2[0], arr1[1] + arr2 [1],...). I created a function to do so but for some reason it is only adding the first array entry correctly. here is the code: </p>  <pre><code>var nums = [566646, 71109, 630748, 804254, 672665, 266232, 127182]; var nums2 = [951445, 884541, 171744, 721337, 609206, 237856, 290200]; var numsLength= nums.length; var i; var sum = 0;  function test() {     for(i=0; i &lt; numsLength; i++) {         sum += (nums[i] + nums2[i]);         console.log(sum);     }; }   test(); </code></pre>